result.execSummary:
The defendant Sarah A. Wilkinson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • Possess Hazardous Substance with the Intent to Abuse Hazardous Substance, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.316(2)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Cases called 13CF337, 14CF30, 14CF56, 14CM113.  Defendant Sarah A. Wilkinson in court, in custody with attorney Alexander Stormont.  Kurt Frederich Klomberg appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Will plead to count 1 in case 13CF337, Ct. 1 on 14cF30, Cts. 1 and 3 on 14CF56.  Court reviews charges/penalties/PQWOR.  Count 1, 13CF337 - DE pleads NC.  14CF30 count 1 - DE pleads NC.  Count 1 and 3 on 14CF56 - DE pleads NC.  Court finds pleas made FVK.  All enhancers are stricken.  Court finds guilty of count 1 on 13cf337, count 1 on 14CF30, and counts 1 and 3 on 14CF56.  All other counts are DRI (including case 14cM113).  Atty. Stormont is heard, Ms. Wilkinson requests first 90 days of jail time only Huber for treatment, not work and no electronic monitoring.  Atty. Klomberg has no objection.  Atty. Klomberg is heard on recommendation.  Atty. Stormont responds.  Ms. Wilkinson does not make statement.  Court is heard and sentence imposed:

On each count:
Sentence withheld,
Probation for 2 years with conditions:
6 months DCJ- with h/t and work priviledge, first 90 days - huber for treatment only and no electronic monitoring (on count 1 - 13cf337), commencing immediately,

AODA,

Possess prescription drugs only under a valid prescription and taken in accordance with prescription, must inform agent of all prescriptions and show all prescriptions in original bottles to agent upon request. 
Restitution to Beaver Dam Fuel of $193.51. (14CM113).
Costs.
DNA sample on felony counts.
Other assessment and counseling as deemed appropriate by agent.  

28 days presenetce credit - count 1 in 14CF56.
Plea/sentencing hearing on March 26, 2014 at 01:00 pm.
